a></b></li>\n<li><b><a href=\"/wiki/Western_esotericism\" title=\"Western esotericism\">Western esotericism</a></b></li></ul>\n</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"navbox-group\" style=\"background-color:#ffd068;border:1px solid #FFFF00;;width:1%\">Anthropological and<br />folkloristic approaches</th><td class=\"navbox-list navbox-odd\" style=\"text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px\"><div style=\"padding:0em 0.25em\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Tanya_Luhrmann\" title=\"Tanya Luhrmann\">Luhrmann's</a> <i><a href=\"/wiki/Persuasions_of_the_Witch%27s_Craft\" title=\"Persuasions of the Witch&#39;s Craft\">Persuasions of the Witch's Craft</a></i> (1989)</li>\n<li>Orion's <i><a href=\"/wiki/Never_Again_the_Burning_Times\" title=\"Never Again the Burning Times\">Never Again the Burning Times</a></i> (1995)</li>\n<li>Hume's <i><a href=\"/wiki/Witchcraft_and_Paganism_in_Australia\" title=\"Witchcraft and Paganism in Australia\">Witchcraft and Paganism in Australia</a></i> (1997)</li>\n<li>Greenwood's <i><a href=\"/wiki/Magic,_Witchcraft_and_the_Otherworld\" title=\"Magic, Witchcraft and the Otherworld\">Magic, Witchcraft and the Otherworld</a></i> (2000)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sabina_Magliocco\" title=\"Sabina Magliocco\">Magliocco's</a> <i><a href=\"/wiki/Witching_Culture\" title=\"Witching Culture\">Witching Culture</a></i> (2004)</li></ul>\n</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"navbox-group\" style=\"background-color:#ffd068;border:1px solid #FFFF00;;width:1%\">Historical approaches</th><td class=\"navbox-list navbox-even\" style=\"text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px\"><div style=\"padding:0em 0.25em\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Ronald_Hutton\" title=\"Ronald Hutton\">Hutton's</a> <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Pagan_Religions_of_the_Ancient_British_Isles\" title=\"The Pagan Religions of the Ancient British Isles\">The Pagan Religions of the Ancient British Isles</a></